def scraper(url: str) -> list:
    """

    :param url: URL of the website to scrape.
    :return: List of dictionaries containing the extracted data.
    """
    # add user agent header to avoid being blocked
    headers = {'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_14_5) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/80.0.3987.149 Safari/537.36'}

    # empty list to store data later
    data = []

    # get page content
    page = requests.get(url, headers=headers)
    soup = BeautifulSoup(page.content, 'html.parser')

    # find all post summary elements
    post_summaries = soup.find_all("div", class_="question-summary")

    # loop through post summaries
    for post in post_summaries:
        try:
            # extract question title
            question_title = post.find("a", class_="question-hyperlink").text.strip()

            # extract tags
            tags = post.find("div", class_="tags").text.strip()

            # extract user name
            user_name = post.find("div", class_="user-details").a.text.strip()

            # extract votes
            votes = post.find("span", class_="vote-count-post").text.strip()

            # extract answers
            answers = post.find("div", class_="status").strong.text.strip()

            # extract views
            views = post.find("div", class_="views").text.split()[0].strip()

            # extract timestamp
            timestamp = post.find("span", class_="relativetime")['title']

            # add data as dictionary to list if not empty
            if question_title and tags and user_name and votes and answers and views and timestamp:
                data.append({
                    "question_title": question_title,
                    "tags": tags,
                    "user_name": user_name,
                    "votes": votes,
                    "answers": answers,
                    "views": views,
                    "timestamp": timestamp
                })
        except Exception as e:
            # print error and continue to next post summary
            print("Error while scraping post: {}".format(e))

    # return data list
    return data

if __name__ == '__main__':
    url = "https://math.stackexchange.com/questions"

    # call scraper function and print returned data as JSON
    data = scraper(url)
    print(json.dumps(data))
